This ‘doctored' text of the first eight plays is practically useless. The ‘Itala recensio,' based in the last twelve plays upon D, seems in the earlier plays to have been based on a MS. that exhibited this ‘doctored' text. All Renaissance MSS. of Plautus are therefore of no value whatsoever as evidence for the text of Plautus, whether in the first eight or in the last twelve plays. Where they diverge from the P›text their reading is due either to a corruption in their original or to conjectura] emendation by their editor.
